(70, 1, '2015-03-10 09:03:39', '2015-03-10 09:03:39', '<strong id="How-RED-Tuition-works">How RED Tuition works</strong>\r\n\r\nRed tuition is a revolution in educational delivery connecting students and tutors live in an interactive online classroom. We cover the complete HSC course for years 11 and 12 for both general and advanced mathematics. We offer weekly tuition as well as 7-day pre exam courses to revise the entire syllabus before exams.\r\n\r\nOnce signed up for weekly tuition, students will receive a username and password enabling them to log in and access their materials. RED Tuition can be easily accessed from any computer or tablet, it is not restricting, students do not need their own individual computer. Each week students will be provided links to their live 1.5 hour lesson, a review sheet with practice questions and study notes.\r\n\r\nThe simplistic design of our online classrooms enables students to work progressively with ease through our straightforward technology. Our structured lessons are viewed live with 10 students to a classroom who may flag the teacher to ask questions at any time throughout the lesson. Each lesson involves explanations of the theory behind each syllabus dot point, followed by example questions demonstrated by the teacher, and quiz questions where students submit an answer. This process is repeated throughout the first hour of each lesson as the class systematically works through the syllabus. The answers submitted by each student appear anonymous to one another, only the teacher may see the results of every student. The students will then work through their review sheet during the final half an hour of the lesson and are encouraged to ask as many questions as possible to make the full use of their tutor.\r\n\r\nIn addition to the 10 lessons per term, RED tuition will provide a free introductory lesson to set goals, plans and acquaint new students with the technology.\r\n\r\nHead tutor, Mitchell Zalai will provide all students with his personal phone number so that if they have any additional questions they can easily contact him over the phone. Similarly, around exam time, he will also open up a webinar on Sundays from 11am-3pm for any further questions or tuition needed by students.\r\n\r\nAt the midpoint and end of each term feedback will be emailed to parents/guardians detailing the progress of each student.\r\n\r\nFinally, we offer online pre exam seminars before the Trials and Final HSC exams. With an expert team we teach the entire maths syllabus over 7 days to refresh students about every type of question that could come up in their exam. Students relearn and practice exam style questions covering the entire syllabus. The days finish by 1:30pm and we strongly advise students to complete a past paper each evening. We provide a compact set of study notes to read over which sums up the entire subject, this coupled with our lectures and finally your own past paper practice in your own time is exactly what you need to prepare for your HSC exams.\r\n\r\n<strong id="Why-RED-Tuition-works>Why RED Tuition works</strong>\r\n\r\nIf you only learn maths at school you will go through the entire syllabus once over a period of 2 years. Without reinforcement how can anyone expect students to retain this knowledge? It is impossible.\r\n\r\nThis is where RED Tuition comes in. Our plan is to reinforce the entire maths syllabus by teaching it to you clearly and in simple ways while providing ample time for students to ask questions and helping students to master concepts via exam style practice questions.\r\n\r\nIf you use RED Tuition you will learn the entire syllabus not just once at school but a second time during our weekly tuition classes, a third time when we have a revision lesson at the end of each term, a fourth time when we host our pre-trials seminars and a fifth time at the pre-HSC seminars. Can you expect RED Tuition students who have gone through the material with teachers five times to retain their knowledge? Absolutely!\r\n\r\nWhy is using RED Tuition more effective than private tuition? With RED tuition you have Mitchell Zalai, 98.85 ATAR, as your personal tutor. He is young, easy to relate to, and has a lot of tutoring experience. He is very accessible – offering his private mobile phone number to all students for any after-hours support. RED Tuition is all about providing a really well planned, structured and organised tuition course which covers every part of the syllabus in depth as opposed to private tutors who usually have no clear vision of their lesson and often just work through questions rather than properly teaching students the underlying concepts. RED Tuition lessons are an hour and a half rather than an hour which is what most private tutors offer. Mitch will stay online on Sundays around exam time for free additional tuition. RED Tuition provides study notes and review sheets for every lesson. We save parents and students travel time and travel expenses. RED Tuition comes at only a fraction of the price of private tutors. We offer hours and hours of seminars in the lead up to HSC trials and Finals whereas private tutors may not have time for any additional lessons. For these reasons, we believe that RED Tuition is a far superior alternative to private tutoring both educationally and financially.\r\n\r\nRED Tuition can be easily accessed from any computer or tablet, it is not restricting, students do not need their own individual computer, you can study from home, at a relative’s house or even at the local library!\r\n\r\nWhen registered with our company, students simply log in to our system and connect live to our scheduled classes. The innovation of our company allows students all over New South Wales to participate accommodating for students living in the city, rurally or studying school at home.\r\n\r\nOur company encourages students who find mathematics difficult as well as high achieving students wanting to reach their full potential.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong id="Vision">Vision</strong>\r\n\r\nWritten in dot points:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Help EVERY Australian student reach their goals</li>\r\n	<li>Inclusive pricing so quality tuition is now affordable for all Australians</li>\r\n	<li>Make tuition easily accessible regardless of location</li>\r\n	<li>Make maths enjoyable, simple and easy to digest</li>\r\n	<li>Help make Australia better at maths</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong id="Meet-the-Team">Meet the Team</strong>', 'About Us', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '12-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-03-10 09:03:39', '2015-03-10 09:03:39', '', 12, 'http://111.93.163.213/RedTution/php/12-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
