(85, 1, '2015-03-10 23:35:09', '2015-03-10 23:35:09', 'Our tuition services provided on our website are under jurisdiction of our terms and conditions. Any use of our services must abide by the obligations outlined below. When registering as a member with RED Tuition you are abiding by our terms and conditions, therefore please read all of the conditions thoroughly in advance to signing up.\r\n\r\n<strong>RED Tuition Information</strong>\r\n\r\nEmail Tutors: <a href="mailto:mitchzalai@redtuition.com.au" class="red-un">mitchzalai@redtuition.com.au</a>\r\n\r\nEmail Administration: <a href="mailto:zoemaddrell@redtuition.com.au" class="red-un">zoemaddrell@redtuition.com.au</a>\r\n\r\nABN: 61 354 805 349\r\n\r\n<strong>Agreement of contract</strong>\r\n\r\nBy signing up to RED Tuition as a member you are accepting to undertake the terms and conditions of which that are bound by this agreement, this also includes our Disclaimer and Privacy Policy.We reserve the right to update or modify these terms at any time. To become a member of RED Tuition you must read the following conditions on which must be applied to the process of registering to our legal contract.\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>a) Read all information located on our website including our Terms and Conditions</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nIt is important for all individuals who are interested in registering to our sight must read the provided details of our services before concluding their registration. This agreement is not a contractual offer, therefore if any information is incorrect we shall not be held liable. RED Tuition reserves the right to change, correct and or modify these mistakes and shall not be held liable to you or any persons. Consequently due to these or any situations RED Tuition will not be held accountable or contractually obliged to provide you with our service on the foundation of erroneous information, including wrong information restated in your membership. It is your obligation to read our legal terms and conditions including our privacy policy from our website in advance to signing up with RED Tuition. If you have any concerns beforehand you may contact us. Before you register as a member of RED Tuition you will be asked whether you agree with our terms and conditions.\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>b) Sign up to RED Tuition by following the prompts on the website and fill in personal details. Your membership will then be established through a confirmation email.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>General Terms</strong>\r\n\r\nBy agreeing to the terms and conditions when signing up as a member of RED Tuition you are accepting to all of our conditions. Therefore we have a right to hold you to the rules of the contract and authorise you only to use the content as have been described within our terms and conditions. Our company does not and will not file any elements of a concluded contract, consequently you should retain a hard copy of the contract. If at any point in time there is a dispute amongst these terms and conditions the remaining terms and conditions will not be affected and still must be implemented. None of the information stated within these terms and conditions are aimed to restrict you, any student or individual to any rights you have as a client.\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>a) General terms bound in agreement of contract</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>We can only present our webinars, review sheets, study notes and any other content in English and not in any other languages</li>\r\n	<li>Courses are based on the NSW syllabus only</li>\r\n	<li>Lessons are scheduled as per RED Tuitions year planner and timetables.</li>\r\n	<li>We only accept Australian dollars</li>\r\n	<li>Payments can be made via Paypal, visa or master card, we do not allow payments in any other way</li>\r\n	<li>We have no legal duty to provide any of our services until all of the fees required have been paid completely</li>\r\n	<li>We reserve the right to vary any of the fees on our website at any given time</li>\r\n	<li>No Refunds except under exceptional circumstances as judged by the founded owners of RED Tuition</li>\r\n	<li>No rude or inappropriate words are to be used within students usernames or used throughout any section of our website. No offensive language may be used when using our webinar services or there will be consequences. We have the right to exclude you from all further tuition if we think it is necessary</li>\r\n	<li>All individuals using the service must be respectful to tutors and other individuals using the service. We have the right to exclude you from all further tuition if we think it is necessary</li>\r\n	<li>Any student/individual who is found intentionally misusing the service for any reason including sending inappropriate messages or hacking will have their membership cancelled without refund</li>\r\n	<li>Users must not share their individual passwords with any other individual. Our membership agreement only validates one student per log in, no exceptions</li>\r\n	<li>We are entitled to refuse registration if we think it is necessary</li>\r\n	<li>We are entitled to exclude students if we think it is necessary</li>\r\n	<li>Your success is your responsibility, we give you certain tools you need to succeed, however it is up to each individual to make the most out of these resources. We do not take any responsibility for review sheets</li>\r\n	<li>We are not legally responsible and will not be held accountable if students do not improve in their grades or exam marks</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>b) Restricted rights of content</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nAll content displayed on the website including audio and visual content on the website, webinars, review sheets and study notes belongs to RED Tuition. All of our content and materials are copyrighted. Students/individuals have consent to:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Display content and materials on a computer/tablet screen to use the services for their own individual use</li>\r\n	<li>Print or store review sheets and or study notes in hard copy or in an electronic form purely for the individuals own purpose</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nUnless you have specific documentation from RED Tuition authorising otherwise, you, students and or individuals do not have authority to:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Issue or dispense any of the content including sharing or duplicating materials</li>\r\n	<li>Issue or dispense any content including audio, visual and written</li>\r\n	<li>Obtain and present, show, copy or print the content for anyone other than themselves</li>\r\n	<li>No student or individual may record any of the audio content from any session</li>\r\n	<li>You must not detach or disengage any of our trademark or copyright notices from our webinars, review sheets, study notes or any of our materials</li>\r\n	<li>Produce a database by downloading and electronically storing or by manual configuration any or all of our materials</li>\r\n	<li>Students/individuals may not redistribute any review sheets or study notes in order to sell them or give them to anyone else</li>\r\n	<li>You must not copy, alter, duplicate, publish, issue, upload to a third party or distribute the content</li>\r\n	<li>You are not allowed to authorise for anyone else to do any of these deeds or actions on your behalf</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>c) Our warranties:</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nAs our services are provided online through technology, it has to be understood that rarely problems, oversights or errors may occur.\r\n\r\nFor these reasons we do not give other warranties in association to our service. These warranties include without limitation to:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>We do not warrant the precision or absoluteness of the content within our services</li>\r\n	<li>Errors may occur with our services this may include problems with our hosting services, live streaming webinar services and or any other problems that may occur</li>\r\n	<li>Take precaution to ensure the process in which you use to get on our website is safeguarded as we do not accept any responsibility for damage or loss due to an unsafe connection from your internet access</li>\r\n	<li>We do not warrant that our services will be free from virus, interference, fraudulent messages/materials or anything with corruptive materials that may cause a direct or indirect loss to yourself or your computer or computer files. Our website may contain outside/third party links, which in no way can we guarantee that these links will be free from harm or contamination as these links are outside and are not controlled by our services and therefore we can not warrant its safety</li>\r\n	<li>We can not warrant that any outside/third party links will not have ads or ad pop-ups. If they do we do not control them or any of their materials that they may show and therefore we will not be held liable to any content within those materials whether appropriate or inappropriate.</li>\r\n	<li>We can not warrant that our scheduled classes will be up running every single lesson. Although we will try our best to do so, their are such reasons for which may be out of our control such as but without restriction to: problems with your internet connections/internet access, problems and or breakdowns with technology systems and network access, blackouts, fires, accidents, floods.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nLimits of Liability\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>d) Our limitation of liability</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nIf a problem with our services arrises, you may inform us and we will do whatever we can, immediately to fix, update or improve the situation. However we will not be held liable for:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>We are not liable to you, any student, guardian or anyone else for any indirect or direct damage, loss, penalty, costs these including losses of money, data, files, photos, opportunity, expected wins/earnings/fortunes whether emerging or in relation to a problem from our service. Under no circumstance (if we are held liable by a court) will more compensation be paid to the individuals involved than they had spent overall