(106, 1, '2015-03-11 00:11:59', '2015-03-11 00:11:59', 'What happens if I sign up midway through a term?\r\nIf you sign up any time throughout a term simply pay for the rest of the term at $15 per week and we will supply you with the study notes for the weeks that you would have missed earlier in the term. For example if you sign up with 5 weeks to go it will cost $75 and we will supply you with the study notes for previous weeks.\r\n\r\nHow many lessons in each term?\r\n10 lessons in each term, plus an extra introductory lesson for new students, plus tutoring available on Sundays around exam times.\r\n\r\nCan I cancel Tuition?\r\nWith RED Tuition you pay upfront for at least one term’s tuition. We will only refund clients under exceptional circumstances. Contact us if you have any questions.\r\n\r\nWhat happens if I can’t attend a class?\r\nIf you know you will be unable to attend a lesson you may be able to switch to an alternate time slot for that week. We will need at least 5 days notice. It is your responsibility to attend all of your lessons on time. If you miss a lesson you can catch up on the work by reading through the supplied study notes and completing the review sheet. There are further opportunities to catch up at the end of term revision lessons and the pre exam seminars.\r\nCan I change time slots?\r\nIf there is space available in other timeslots you can change no questions asked.\r\n\r\nIf I drop from Advanced Maths to General Maths can I change to General Maths Tuition?\r\nYes, but as long as there is a space available in a General Maths class.\r\n\r\nWhat equipment will I require?\r\nPlease refer to www.blablabla.com to view the requirements for using webinar. Once we know what webinar program we will use we will detail a few specifics down.\r\n\r\nDo you offer any other subjects besides year 11 and 12 maths?\r\nAt the moment we are focussed purely on the HSC General and Advanced maths syllabus, however we are looking to expand in the future.\r\n\r\nIs it NSW only?\r\nFor 2015, Red Tuition is based on the NSW HSC Curriculum. There are opportunities to eventually expand across Australia and we hope to do so in the near future.', 'FAQ', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '82-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-03-11 00:11:59', '2015-03-11 00:11:59', '', 82, 'http://111.93.163.213/RedTution/php/82-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
